By BO Staff Writer Article 82 of the Venezuelan Constitution provides: “Every person has the right to a home which is adequate, safe, and comfortable, hygienic, with essential basic services, which include a habitat that humanizes family, neighborhood and community relationships.” President Maduro led the delivery on 5 December 2020 in the La Gran Villa urban development of the 3,300,000th house of the Great Venezuela Housing Mission (GMVV). Read here: https://www.telesurenglish.net/…/venezuelan-housing…